SIMPLE: whiplash
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whiplash
<hw>Whip"lash`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
lash of a whip, -- usually made of thongs of leather, or of cords,
braided or twisted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a sudden change of direction, resembling the motion
of the tip of a whip when it is cracked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a stinging psychological effect reminiscent of being
stung by a whip.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>a <er>whiplash injury</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whiplash injury</ent>⟦br⟧
